WEBVTT

p01
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.528
The Sales module keeps nine pages in one sidebar, all under the header Transactions.

p02
00:00:06.227 --> 00:00:13.618
You already know the first one, Tickets, from the last two lessons,

p03
00:00:14.387 --> 00:00:15.797
and the new Refund Approvals page waits for a lesson of its own.

p04
00:00:16.302 --> 00:00:17.079
That leaves seven for today: line items, payments, cash out, drawers,

p05
00:00:17.442 --> 00:00:18.006
declines, gift cards, and house accounts.

p06
00:00:18.537 --> 00:00:19.137
This is a map, not a deep dive.

p07
00:00:19.675 --> 00:00:29.625
By the end you'll open the right one without thinking.

p08
00:00:30.080 --> 00:00:32.579
Start where you already are, on Ticket Details.

p09
00:00:32.579 --> 00:00:35.783
Tickets gave you one row per sale.

p10
00:00:35.783 --> 00:00:39.220
This page breaks each sale open: one row per line rung.

p11
00:00:39.220 --> 00:00:41.402
Every service, every discount, every adjustment,

p12
00:00:41.402 --> 00:00:44.134
with the cashier and location right beside it.

p13
00:00:44.134 --> 00:00:49.230
When a customer questions a charge and you need to see what was actually rung,

p14
00:00:49.230 --> 00:00:52.666
not just the total, this is the view that shows it.

p15
00:00:53.214 --> 00:00:54.320
Click Payments.

p16
00:00:54.643 --> 00:00:58.333
Every completed payment across the network, searchable by ticket number.

p17
00:00:58.630 --> 00:01:01.644
Method and amount tell you how a given sale was tendered: card, cash, or account.

p18
00:01:01.882 --> 00:01:03.662
One thing to hold onto: this page only records payments that went through.

p19
00:01:04.040 --> 00:01:05.298
Approvals and declines aren't its job.

p20
00:01:05.526 --> 00:01:14.436
Declines are tracked on their own page, which is exactly where we go next.

p21
00:01:15.040 --> 00:01:16.298
Now Payouts.

p22
00:01:17.038 --> 00:01:20.128
This is cash leaving the drawer instead of coming into it:

p23
00:01:20.523 --> 00:01:21.388
petty cash, or a vendor paid on delivery.

p24
00:01:21.697 --> 00:01:23.321
Read across the columns and you see why it matters.

p25
00:01:24.412 --> 00:01:27.043
Every payout is stamped with a shift number, a cashier, and the terminal it came from.

p26
00:01:27.712 --> 00:01:38.480
That trail is what lets a manager account for cash that left the register during a shift.

p27
00:01:38.935 --> 00:01:39.885
Click Shifts.

p28
00:01:40.235 --> 00:01:42.050
Notice the page gets simpler here: one count, no charts.

p29
00:01:42.342 --> 00:01:44.132
A shift is a single drawer session, opened and closed on one terminal.

p30
00:01:44.657 --> 00:01:48.694
This is where you live when a drawer won't balance.

p31
00:01:48.992 --> 00:01:55.634
Opening cash, closing cash, and every payment and payout in between,

p32
00:01:55.953 --> 00:01:59.680
that's the reconciliation, and this page lines it up in one row.

p33
00:02:00.132 --> 00:02:01.486
Here's the page I promised, the Declined Credit Card Log.

p34
00:02:01.689 --> 00:02:03.380
A member swears they paid, but their account shows nothing.

p35
00:02:04.075 --> 00:02:07.306
Start here, every time.

p36
00:02:07.601 --> 00:02:09.431
The reason column tells you why the card was turned down,

p37
00:02:10.528 --> 00:02:18.136
and the attempts column tells you how many times the system retried before it gave up.

p38
00:02:18.527 --> 00:02:21.840
That usually answers the question before you even call the gateway.

p39
00:02:22.240 --> 00:02:24.182
Click Gift Card Transactions.

p40
00:02:24.734 --> 00:02:28.092
Every load and every redeem against a gift card lands here.

p41
00:02:28.586 --> 00:02:33.815
Type a card number into search and you get its whole history,

p42
00:02:34.407 --> 00:02:36.837
with the running balance after each line.

p43
00:02:37.128 --> 00:02:40.272
One caveat the page states in plain sight: this is completed activity, not card status.

p44
00:02:40.706 --> 00:02:46.091
To issue a card or check whether it's active, that's CRM Gift Cards, a different page.

p45
00:02:46.560 --> 00:02:48.995
Last page, House Account Transactions.

p46
00:02:49.458 --> 00:02:52.631
These are sales billed to an account instead of paid at the register,

p47
00:02:53.087 --> 00:02:55.358
the fleets and businesses that run on terms.

p48
00:02:56.089 --> 00:02:58.817
Each row ties a ticket to the account that owes for it.

p49
00:02:59.343 --> 00:03:03.752
That's the feed behind the balances and the invoices you'll work in CRM House Accounts.

p50
00:03:04.400 --> 00:03:06.080
Here, it's just the raw charges.

p51
00:03:06.537 --> 00:03:07.310
That's the map.

p52
00:03:07.704 --> 00:03:11.572
Nine pages in the sidebar, and seven of them answer a question you'll hear.

p53
00:03:11.998 --> 00:03:13.236
Line items on a sale? Ticket Details.

p54
00:03:13.811 --> 00:03:14.734
How was it paid? Payments.

p55
00:03:15.104 --> 00:03:16.022
Cash out of the drawer? Payouts.

p56
00:03:16.445 --> 00:03:17.013
Drawer won't balance? Shifts.

p57
00:03:17.329 --> 00:03:18.337
Says they paid but we show declined? The Declined log.

p58
00:03:18.807 --> 00:03:19.429
Tracing a gift card? Gift Card Transactions.

p59
00:03:19.789 --> 00:03:20.944
Billed to an account? House Account Transactions.

p60
00:03:21.299 --> 00:03:21.844
Learn the map now, because for the rest of your support work,

p61
00:03:22.297 --> 00:03:37.840
knowing the right page is half the job.

